I've found two issues in your code that need to be fixed.

Firstly, you need to remove the `using System.Data.OleDb;` line at the top of your code, as it is already included in the line above. So remove the duplicate line:

```csharp
using System.Data.OleDb;
```

Secondly, I suggest using named parameters instead of using the question mark symbol since Microsoft Access sometimes might be picky about it. Here's the modified code snippet that should fix the OleDbException issue:

```csharp
