When modifying the code to work with MySQL, an important thing to consider is using the proper components for MySQL connection, queries, and database handling. In this case, it is recommended to use the `TFDConnection`, `TFDQuery`, and other FireDAC components instead of the ADO components.

For example, you can replace `TADOConnection` with `TFDConnection` and `TADOQuery` with `TFDQuery`. The `TDataSource`, `TDBGrid`, and other components can stay the same since they work with both ADO and FireDAC.

Here is an example of how you can modify the code to use FireDAC components:

1. Replace `TADOConnection` with `TFDConnection` and configure it to connect to your MySQL server. You can do this by setting the `Params` property with your MySQL server configuration (host, user, password, database).
2. Replace `TADOQuery` with `TFDQuery` and set its `Connection` property to the `TFDConnection` you created earlier.
3. Update the database operations (create, load, add, update, delete) to use the FireDAC components. Most of the code will stay the same, but you will need to replace references to ADO components with the corresponding FireDAC components.

Here is an example of how you can create a connection to a MySQL server using FireDAC components:

```cpp
void OpenConnection()
{
    String c = "Pooled=True;" + // Set pooled (use connection pool)
               "DriverID=MySQL;" + // Set driver for MySQL
               "Server=localhost;" + // Set server address, port and database name
               "Port=3306;" +
               "Database=catalog;" +
               "User_Name=root;" + // Set user name and password
               "Password=1234";

    try
    {
        FConnection->Params->Values["Database"] = "catalog"; 
        FConnection->Params->Values["User_Name"] = "root"; 
        FConnection->Params->Values["Password"] = "1234"; 
        FConnection->Connected = true; 
    }
    catch (Exception &e) 
    {
        ShowMessage("Error connecting to the MySQL database: " + e.Message);
    }
}
```

Keep in mind that FireDAC requires a different set of components, so you need to include the proper headers and link the appropriate libraries in your project.

To use FireDAC components to connect to a MySQL database, you will also need to properly set up the database drivers. For more information, please refer to the Embarcadero documentation:

- [FireDAC MySQL Phys Driver - Embarcadero](https://docwiki.embarcadero.com/RADStudio/Sydney/en/FireDAC_MySQL_Phis_Driver)
- [Connect to MySQL Server (FireDAC) - Embarcadero](https://docwiki.embarcadero.com/CodeExamples/Sydney/en/FireDAC.MySQL_Sample)

在 C# 中，可以使用 `String.Compare` 方法来比较两个字符串，同时设置 `StringComparison.OrdinalIgnoreCase` 选项，这将会忽略大小写来进行比较。

例如，下面的代码将会比较两个字符串 `str1` 和 `str2`，忽略它们的大小写：

```csharp
string str1 = "Hello";
string str2 = "hello";

bool areEqual = (string.Compare(str1, str2, StringComparison.OrdinalIgnoreCase) == 0);

if (areEqual)
{
    Console.WriteLine("The two strings are equal, ignoring case.");
}
else
{
    Console.WriteLine("The two strings are not equal, ignoring case.");
}
```

在上面的例子中，我们使用 `string.Compare` 方法来比较两个字符串，同时设置 `StringComparison.OrdinalIgnoreCase` 选项，这将会忽略大小写来进行比较。

`string.Compare` 方法将返回一个整数值，如果两个字符串相等则返回 0，否则返回非零值。因此，我们检查 `string.Compare` 的返回值是否等于 0，以确定这两个字符串是否相等。

